{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a specific criminal offence for failing to provide a reliable survey",
        "additional_details": "Without stricter penalties, there is potential for conflicts of interest, danger of undermining evidence & using misleading information as reports & information generated by them are treated as indisputable. In 2017 the High Court found an expert unreliable & lacking independence, which demonstrates that surveyors/structural engineers do not always perform their roles to the highest standard: https://hsfnotes.com/litigation/2017/07/24/high-court-finds-expert-unreliable-and-lacking-independence",
        "background": "The Government must urgently introduce a specific criminal offence for property surveyors/engineers who knowingly make/legitimise inaccurate/misleading reports, to ensure impartiality and reliability.",
